HEADWORD: Knight-errant
<hw>Knight"-er`rant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Knight-errants</plw>, or <plw>Knights-errant</plw>.</plu> <def>A
wandering knight; a knight who traveled in search of adventures, for the
purpose of exhibiting military skill, prowess, and generosity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

